imdb.title: What Matters?
plot: Annual documentary special on Australian children competing in an essay competition.

Each year the _What Matters?_ (qv) Competition, run by the Whitlam Institute asks the question to students in years 5 to 12 across NSW and the ACT: "Tell us what matters to you in 400-600 words?" The competition is inspired by former Prime Minister Gough Whitlam's determination to involve the people of Australia in shaping the nation's future.
